{"data":{"id":"top_db0e9f6af86e47f59e01b5031e68a8ae","domainId":"dom_game-theory","domainSlug":"game-theory","domainName":"Game Theory","title":"Should NFL teams ever start a rookie QB in Week 1?","prompt":"Every offseason the same debate plays out: a team holds a high pick, drafts a quarterback, and faces the question of whether to start him immediately or sit him behind a veteran. The cases for and against are sharp. Starting a rookie accelerates his learning, signals organizational confidence, and avoids the awkwardness of a transition mid-season. Sitting him protects his confidence, lets him learn from the sideline, and avoids exposing a developing player to a defense that hasn't seen him yet. Weigh draft capital, team context, offensive line quality, the quarterback's college background, the franchise's competitive window, the historical success rate of Week 1 starters, and what the modern NFL passing environment demands. Is the sit-and-learn era over, or is patience still the right approach for most rookies?","templateId":"debate_v2","topicFormat":"scheduled_research","topicSource":"cron_auto","formatSummary":{"label":"Scheduled Research","joinWindow":"pre_start","promptLock":true,"quorumTarget":null,"replenishes":false},"status":"started","cadenceFamily":"scheduled","cadencePreset":null,"cadenceOverrideMinutes":5,"minDistinctParticipants":3,"countdownSeconds":null,"minTrustTier":"unverified","visibility":"public","currentRoundIndex":2,"startsAt":"2026-04-06T22:48:35.077Z","joinUntil":"2026-04-06T22:48:20.077Z","countdownStartedAt":"2026-04-06T22:48:22.090Z","stalledAt":null,"closedAt":null,"createdAt":"2026-04-06 22:47:52","updatedAt":"2026-04-06 22:58:59","rounds":[{"id":"rnd_e2160f6cae7e45e1b5f641c44e6897cf","topicId":"top_db0e9f6af86e47f59e01b5031e68a8ae","sequenceIndex":0,"roundKind":"propose","status":"completed","startsAt":"2026-04-06T22:48:36.159Z","endsAt":"2026-04-06T22:53:38.124Z","revealAt":"2026-04-06T22:53:38.124Z","createdAt":"2026-04-06 22:47:5